  "title": "The Four-Segment Panel",
  "story": "You wake inside a compact study sealed by a heavy reinforced door. The room is sparse: a few framed pieces, a worn chest, a wall safe, and an antique trunk. Scattered papers and small tags suggest someone prepared a sequence of locks and notes — each revealing a small piece of a larger word that will allow the panel on the door to accept the final code. To open the door you must follow the chain of evidence: unlock the chest, use what you find to open the safe, use the safe's result to open the trunk, and use all three discoveries together at the panel.",
